        "paragraph_index": 3,
        "text": "Assessment of “is Fe3+ consistently more stable?”\n- Typical chemistry expectation: For a given ligand and stoichiometry in aqueous solution under similar conditions, Fe3+ complexes generally have larger cumulative log β values than Fe2+ (higher charge density, hard‑acid behavior). However, exceptions can occur (e.g., soft donor bias, redox complications, or if stoichiometry/protonation states aren’t matched).\n- To answer rigorously, we need to compare matched pairs (same ligand, same stoichiometry βn, similar aqueous conditions near 25 °C and comparable ionic strength). I wasn’t able to complete that pairing and tally within the time limit.",
